The Federal Government is in the process of approving new regulation and operational guidelines for the National Lottery Commission, the Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha, said. He explained that this was to strengthen the capacity of the commission and the National Lottery Trust Fund to perform their functions effectively. He said this at Umuezeoka General Hospital in Ezza North Local Government of Ebonyi State where he presented medical equipment. Mustapha, represented by the permanent secretary, Special Duties, Office of SGF, Williams Alo, charged operators and organisations engaged in lottery businesses to sit up or lose their licences.